No such lemma appears to exist in Mathlib. The premise of your question is likely flawed or conflating two distinct results. Mathlib does have `IsCompact.closure [T2Space α] {s : Set α} (hs : IsCompact s) : IsCompact (closure s)` (file: `Mathlib/Topology/Compactness/Compact.lean`), which shows the closure of a compact set in a Hausdorff space is compact — not sequentially Polish. Separately, `PolishSpace` results live in `Mathlib/Topology/MetricSpace/Polish.lean`, where e.g. `IsClosed.polishSpace` shows a closed subset of a Polish space is Polish, but this requires the ambient space to already be Polish, not merely a Hausdorff topological group. There is no single lemma combining "compact set", "Hausdorff topological group", and "sequentially Polish closure" — I was unable to locate one in Mathlib4's docs or source, and fabricating a name would be incorrect.
